            <p><strong>Uranus:</strong> 3.7 arcsecond greenish disk, visible at 100x+, moderate challenge. Moons require 8+ inches and dark skies. Oppositions annually in October-November timeframe (varies by year).</p>
            <p><strong>Neptune:</strong> 2.3 arcsecond blue disk, requires 150x+ to resolve confidently, greater challenge. Triton visible in 8+ inches. Oppositions annually in August-September timeframe.</p>
            <p><strong>Value:</strong> These observations provide perspective on solar system scale and remind observers of worlds that only spacecraft have visited closely. The challenge itself holds satisfaction.</p>
